rts-bill-into-law |url-status=live }}</ref> Oklahoma,<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.nbcnews.com/nbc-out/out-politics-and-policy/oklahoma-governor-signs-transgender-sports-ban-rcna22210 | title=Oklahoma governor signs transgender sports ban | website=[[NBC News]] | date=March 30, 2022 | access-date=June 19, 2023 | archive-date=April 22, 2023 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230422114049/https://www.nbcnews.com/nbc-out/out-politics-and-policy/oklahoma-governor-signs-transgender-sports-ban-rcna22210 | url-status=live }}</ref> Kentucky,<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.nbcnews.com/nbc-out/out-politics-and-policy/kentucky-legislature-overrides-governors-veto-transgender-sports-ban-rcna24303 | title=Kentucky Legislature overrides governor's veto of transgender sports ban | website=[[NBC News]] | date=April 13, 2022 | access-date=June 19, 2023 | archive-date=June 18, 2023 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230618020959/https://www.nbcnews.com/nbc-out/out-politics-and-policy/kentucky-legislature-overrides-governors-veto-transgender-sports-ban-rcna24303 | url-status=live }}</ref> Mississippi,<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.nbcnews.com/feature/nbc-out/mississippi-governor-signs-bill-banning-trans-athletes-school-sports-n1260709 | title=Mississippi governor signs bill banning trans athletes from school sports | website=[[NBC News]] | date=March 11, 2021 | access-date=June 19, 2023 | archive-date=June 8, 2023 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230608230140/http://www.nbcnews.com/feature/nbc-out/mississippi-governor-signs-bill-banning-trans-athletes-school-sports-n1260709 | url-status=live }}</ref> Tennessee,<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.si.com/college/2022/05/06/tennessee-governor-signs-legislation-banning-collegiate-transgender-athletes | title=Tennessee Governor Signs Legislation Banning Collegiate Transgender Athletes | newspaper=Sports Illustrated | date=May 6, 2022 | access-date=June 19, 2023 | archive-date=April 18, 2023 | archive-ur